{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":739,"text":"Has anyone among you\never been exposed to tear gas?"},{"time":5318,"text":"Tear gas? Anyone?"},{"time":8433,"text":"I'm sorry to hear that, so you might know\nthat it's a very toxic substance,"},{"time":13004,"text":"but you might not know\nthat it's a very simple molecule"},{"time":16428,"text":"with an unpronouncable name:"},{"time":18642,"text":"it's called chlorobenzalmalononitrile."},{"time":21762,"text":"\nI made it."},{"time":23779,"text":"It's decades old, but it's becoming\nvery trendy among police forces"},{"time":29137,"text":"around the planet lately, it seems,"},{"time":32016,"text":"and according to my experience\nas a non-voluntary breather of it,"},{"time":36753,"text":"tear gas has two main\nbut quite opposite effects."},{"time":41026,"text":"One, it can really burn your eyes,"},{"time":44168,"text":"and two, it can also\nhelp you to open them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48603,"text":"Tear gas definitely helped\nto open mine to something"},{"time":52192,"text":"that I want to share\nwith you this afternoon:"},{"time":55932,"text":"that livestreaming the power\nof independent broadcasts through the web"},{"time":61226,"text":"can be a game-changer in journalism,"},{"time":64407,"text":"in activism, and as I see it,\nin the political discourse as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70749,"text":"That idea started \nto dawn on me in early 2011"},{"time":75522,"text":"when I was covering\na protest in São Paulo."},{"time":79060,"text":"It was the marijuana march,"},{"time":81048,"text":"a gathering of people asking\nfor the legalization of cannabis."},{"time":85010,"text":"When that group started to move,"},{"time":87475,"text":"the riot police came from the back\nwith rubber bullets, bombs,"},{"time":91785,"text":"and then the gas."},{"time":94184,"text":"But to make a long story short,"},{"time":96202,"text":"I had entered that protest\nas the editor-in-chief"},{"time":100091,"text":"of a well-established printed magazine\nwhere I'd worked for 11 years,"},{"time":104864,"text":"and thanks to this unsolicited\neffects of tear gas,"},{"time":109776,"text":"I left it as a journalist that was now\ncommitted to new ways"},{"time":114709,"text":"of sharing the raw experience\nof what it's like to be there, actually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120652,"text":"So in the following week,\nI was back in the streets,"},{"time":124492,"text":"but that time, I wasn't a member\nof any media outlet anymore."},{"time":128555,"text":"I was there as an independent\nlivestreamer, and all I had with me"},{"time":133176,"text":"was basically borrowed equipment."},{"time":135312,"text":"I had a very simple camera\nand a backpack with 3G modems."},{"time":141366,"text":"And I had this weblink\nthat could be shared through social media,"},{"time":146991,"text":"could be put in any website,"},{"time":149868,"text":"and that time,\nthe protest went along fine."},{"time":152897,"text":"There was no violence."},{"time":154746,"text":"There was no action scenes."},{"time":156835,"text":"But there was something really exciting,"},{"time":159274,"text":"because I could see at a distance\nthe TV channels covering it,"},{"time":164124,"text":"and they had these big vans\nand the teams and the cameras,"},{"time":168148,"text":"and I was basically doing the same thing"},{"time":170627,"text":"and all I had was a backpack."},{"time":173403,"text":"And that was really\nexciting to a journalist,"},{"time":176678,"text":"but the most interesting part\nwas when I got back home, actually,"},{"time":181059,"text":"because I learned that I had been watched"},{"time":183886,"text":"by more than 90,000 people,"},{"time":186990,"text":"and I got hundreds of emails and messages\nof people asking me, basically,"},{"time":191895,"text":"how did I do it,"},{"time":193295,"text":"how it was possible to do such a thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196611,"text":"And I learned something else,\nthat that was actually the first time"},{"time":199884,"text":"that somebody had ever done\na livestreaming in a street protest"},{"time":205022,"text":"in the country."},{"time":207216,"text":"And that really shocked me,"},{"time":209758,"text":"because I was no geek,\nI was no technology guy,"},{"time":213536,"text":"and all the equipment needed\nwas already there,"},{"time":216295,"text":"was easily available."},{"time":218501,"text":"And I realized that\nwe had a frontier here,"},{"time":221617,"text":"a very important one,"},{"time":223080,"text":"that it was just a matter\nof changing the perspective,"},{"time":226237,"text":"and the web could be actually used,"},{"time":228466,"text":"already used, as a colossal\nand uncontrollable"},{"time":231908,"text":"and highly anarchical TV channel,\nTV network,"},{"time":235721,"text":"and anyone with very basic skills\nand very basic equipment,"},{"time":240905,"text":"even someone like me who had this\nlittle stuttering issue,"},{"time":246748,"text":"so if it happens, bear with me please,"},{"time":250873,"text":"even someone like me\ncould become a broadcaster."},{"time":255392,"text":"And that sounded revolutionary in my mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257584,"text":"So for the next couple of years,"},{"time":259162,"text":"I started to experiment with\nlivestreaming in different ways,"},{"time":263209,"text":"not only in the streets\nbut mostly in studios and in homes,"},{"time":266815,"text":"until the beginning of 2013, last year,"},{"time":270123,"text":"when I became the cofounder of a group\ncalled Mídia NINJA."},{"time":274303,"text":"NINJA is an acronym"},{"time":275752,"text":"that stands for Narrativas Independentes \nJornalismo e Ação,"},{"time":279582,"text":"or in English, independent narratives,\njournalism, and action."},{"time":283493,"text":"It was a media group\nthat had little media plan."},{"time":287415,"text":"We didn't have any financial structure."},{"time":289464,"text":"We were not planning\nto make money out of this,"},{"time":292644,"text":"which was wise, because you shouldn't\ntry to make money out of journalism now."},{"time":298484,"text":"But we had a very solid\nand clear conviction,"},{"time":301188,"text":"that we knew that the hyperconnected\nenvironment of social media"},{"time":306142,"text":"could maybe allow us to consolidate"},{"time":308773,"text":"a network of experimental journalists\nthroughout the country."},{"time":314117,"text":"So we launched a Facebook page first,\nand then a manifesto,"},{"time":319254,"text":"and started to cover the streets\nin a very simple way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322992,"text":"But then something happened,\nsomething that wasn't predicted,"},{"time":327310,"text":"that no one could have anticipated."},{"time":329817,"text":"Street protests started\nto erupt in São Paulo."},{"time":332737,"text":"They began as very local and specific."},{"time":334917,"text":"They were against the bus fare hike\nthat had just happened in the city."},{"time":340227,"text":"This is a bus."},{"time":342138,"text":"It's written there, \"Theft.\""},{"time":345102,"text":"But those kind of manifestations\nstarted to grow,"},{"time":350161,"text":"and they kept happening."},{"time":351996,"text":"So the police violence against them\nstarted to grow as well."},{"time":356803,"text":"But there was another conflict,"},{"time":358512,"text":"the one I believe that's\nmore important here"},{"time":361016,"text":"to make my point that\nit was a narrative conflict."},{"time":364976,"text":"There was this mainstream media\nversion of the facts"},{"time":368006,"text":"that anyone who was on the streets\ncould easily challenge"},{"time":372292,"text":"if they presented their own vision\nof what was actually happening there."},{"time":378561,"text":"And it was this clash of visions,\nthis clash of narratives,"},{"time":381641,"text":"that I think turned those protests"},{"time":384983,"text":"into a long period in the country\nof political reckoning"},{"time":388824,"text":"where hundreds of thousands of people,"},{"time":392332,"text":"probably more than a million people"},{"time":394150,"text":"took to the streets in the whole country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397638,"text":"But it wasn't about\nthe bus fare hike anymore."},{"time":400252,"text":"It was about everything."},{"time":403796,"text":"The people's demands, their expectations,"},{"time":406246,"text":"the reasons why they were on the streets"},{"time":408396,"text":"could be as diverse as they could\nbe contradictory in many cases."},{"time":413235,"text":"If you could read it,\nyou would understand me."},{"time":417343,"text":"But it was in this environment\nof political catharsis"},{"time":421738,"text":"that the country was going through"},{"time":424687,"text":"that it had to do with politics, indeed,"},{"time":427984,"text":"but it had to do also\nwith a new way of organizing,"},{"time":432017,"text":"through a new way of communicating."},{"time":434950,"text":"It was in that environment\nthat Mídia NINJA emerged"},{"time":437752,"text":"from almost anonymity\nto become a national phenomenon,"},{"time":442435,"text":"because we did have the right equipment."},{"time":445288,"text":"We are not using big cameras."},{"time":447488,"text":"We are using basically this."},{"time":450112,"text":"We are using smartphones."},{"time":452111,"text":"And that, actually, allowed us to become\ninvisible in the middle of the protests,"},{"time":457019,"text":"but it allowed us to do something else:"},{"time":459701,"text":"to show what it was like\nto be in the protests,"},{"time":463525,"text":"to present to people at home\na subjective perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469279,"text":"But there was something\nthat is more important,"},{"time":471615,"text":"I think, than the equipment."},{"time":472971,"text":"It was our mindset,"},{"time":475699,"text":"because we are not behaving\nas a media outlet."},{"time":478870,"text":"We are not competing for news."},{"time":480808,"text":"We are trying to encourage people,"},{"time":483129,"text":"to invite people,\nand to actually teach people"},{"time":485985,"text":"how to do this, how they also\ncould become broadcasters."},{"time":490195,"text":"And that was crucial to turn Mídia NINJA\nfrom a small group of people,"},{"time":496265,"text":"and in a matter of weeks,"},{"time":497915,"text":"we multiplied and we grew\nexponentially throughout the country."},{"time":502492,"text":"So in a matter of a week or two,\nas the protests kept happening,"},{"time":507169,"text":"we were hundreds of young people"},{"time":509381,"text":"connected in this network\nthroughout the country."},{"time":512186,"text":"We were covering more than\n50 cities at the same time."},{"time":515326,"text":"That's something that\nno TV channel could ever do."},{"time":518980,"text":"That was responsible\nfor turning us suddenly, actually,"},{"time":522393,"text":"into kind of the mainstream\nmedia of social media."},{"time":527319,"text":"So we had a couple of thousands\nof followers on our Facebook page,"},{"time":531370,"text":"and soon we had a quarter\nof a million followers."},{"time":534606,"text":"Our posts and our videos"},{"time":536290,"text":"were being seen by more than\n11 million timelines a week."},{"time":540269,"text":"It was way more than any newspaper\nor any magazine could ever do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545990,"text":"And that turned Mídia NINJA\ninto something else,"},{"time":549234,"text":"more than a media outlet,\nthan a media project."},{"time":552675,"text":"It became almost like a public service"},{"time":555434,"text":"to the citizen, to the protester,"},{"time":557961,"text":"to the activist,"},{"time":559695,"text":"because they had a very simple\nand efficient and peaceful tool"},{"time":563123,"text":"to confront both police\nand media authority."},{"time":569644,"text":"Many of our images started \nto be used in regular TV channels."},{"time":573643,"text":"Our livestreams started to be broadcast\neven in regular televisions"},{"time":578474,"text":"when things got really rough."},{"time":580433,"text":"Some our images were responsible\nto take some people out of jail,"},{"time":585730,"text":"people who were being arrested unfairly"},{"time":588569,"text":"under false accusations,\nand we could prove them innocent."},{"time":592338,"text":"And that also turned Mídia NINJA very soon"},{"time":595579,"text":"to be seen as almost\nan enemy of cops, unfortunately,"},{"time":599590,"text":"and we started to be severely beaten,\nand eventually arrested on the streets."},{"time":604663,"text":"It happened in many cases."},{"time":606577,"text":"But that was also useful,\nbecause we were still at the web,"},{"time":610909,"text":"so that helped to trigger\nan important debate in the country"},{"time":616094,"text":"on the role of the media itself"},{"time":618543,"text":"and the state of the freedom\nof the press in the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622142,"text":"So Mídia NINJA now evolved"},{"time":624093,"text":"and finally consolidated itself\nin what we hoped it would become:"},{"time":630143,"text":"a national network\nof hundreds of young people,"},{"time":633427,"text":"self-organizing themselves locally"},{"time":637304,"text":"to cover social, human rights issues,"},{"time":641065,"text":"and expressing themselves\nnot only politically"},{"time":643833,"text":"but journalistically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648665,"text":"What I started to do\nin the beginning of this year,"},{"time":653000,"text":"as Mídia NINJA is already\na self-organizing network,"},{"time":657156,"text":"I'm dedicating myself to another project."},{"time":660589,"text":"It's called Fluxo,\nwhich is Portuguese for \"stream.\""},{"time":663835,"text":"It's a journalism studio\nin São Paulo downtown,"},{"time":666642,"text":"where I used livestream to experiment"},{"time":669969,"text":"with what I call post-television formats."},{"time":673474,"text":"But I'm also trying to come up with ways\nto finance independent journalism"},{"time":678852,"text":"through a direct relationship\nwith an audience,"},{"time":681664,"text":"with an active audience,"},{"time":683626,"text":"because now I really want\nto try to make a living"},{"time":686296,"text":"out of my tear gas resolution back then."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690058,"text":"But there's something\nmore significant here,"},{"time":692348,"text":"something that I believe is more important\nand more crucial than my personal example."},{"time":697794,"text":"I said that livestream could turn the web\ninto a colossal TV network,"},{"time":702629,"text":"but I believe it does something else,"},{"time":704666,"text":"because after watching people using it,"},{"time":707627,"text":"not only to cover things but to express,\nto organize themselves politically,"},{"time":713651,"text":"I believe livestream can turn cyberspace\ninto a global political arena"},{"time":720419,"text":"where everyone might have a voice,"},{"time":722803,"text":"a proper voice,"},{"time":724347,"text":"because livestream takes the monopoly\nof the broadcast political discourse,"},{"time":729832,"text":"of the verbal aspect\nof the political dialogue"},{"time":732585,"text":"out of the mouths of just politicians\nand political pundits alone,"},{"time":738194,"text":"and it empowers the citizen\nthrough this direct and non-mediated power"},{"time":743664,"text":"of exchanging experiences and dialogue,"},{"time":746647,"text":"empowers them to question\nand to influence authorities"},{"time":750697,"text":"in ways in which we are about to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754226,"text":"And I believe it does something else\nthat might be even more important,"},{"time":758780,"text":"that the simplicity of the technology\ncan merge objectivity and subjectivity"},{"time":765470,"text":"in a very political way, as I see it,"},{"time":768133,"text":"because it really helps the audience,"},{"time":773302,"text":"the citizen, to see the world\nthrough somebody else's eye,"},{"time":777796,"text":"so it helps the citizen\nto put him- or herself"},{"time":781230,"text":"in other people's place."},{"time":783902,"text":"And that idea, I think, \nshould be the intention,"},{"time":787170,"text":"should be the goal of any good journalism,\nany good activism,"},{"time":791885,"text":"but most of all, any good politics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794537,"text":"Thank you very much. It was an honor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797065,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}